
[1]irreligious

   IRRELIG'IOUS, a. Destitute of religious principles; condemning
   religion; impious; ungodly.

   Shame and reproach are generally the portion of the impious and
   irreligious.

   1. Contrary to religion; profane; impious; wicked; as an irreligious
   speech; irreligious conduct.
